   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Introduction
  </section>
  <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00013"
     rolemaps-to="Part"
    >
   <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.00014"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
      rolemaps-to="P"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Wright’s protocol has been successfully recast in terms of spatial domains con­taining all (or at least many) of the conceivable morphological variants (‘mor­phospaces’ 
    <Em xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
       id="ID.00015"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>sensu
    </Em>
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> ?TR93 ()).
   </text>
  </text-unit>
  <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00016"
     rolemaps-to="Part"
    >
   <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.00017"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
      rolemaps-to="P"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>In this paper, I review the construction of a morphospace for early land plants (?NK84; ?N97-adaptive-walks; ?N97-effects) and show how it can be used ….
   </text>
  </text-unit>
  <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00018"
     rolemaps-to="Part"
    >
   <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.00019"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
      rolemaps-to="P"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>… horizontally cantilevered branches impose the largest bending moments on subtending branches (?N92; ?N94-allometry).
   </text>
  </text-unit>
  <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00020"
     rolemaps-to="Part"
    >
   <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.00021"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
      rolemaps-to="P"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>… This definition removes the sharp dichotomy said to exist between ‘object’ and ‘process’ complexity (i.e. the number of different parts in an organic system versus the number of different interactions among them (?M96)).
   </text>
  </text-unit>
  <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00022"
     rolemaps-to="Part"
    >
   <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.00023"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
      rolemaps-to="P"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>… fossil record for Devonian and Carboniferous vascular land plants (?NTK80; ?NTK83; ?GA84).
   </text>
  </text-unit>
